cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on the diffusion of emerging technologies and uses publication records to study the mechanisms of diffusion. The methods for analyzing and visualizing geographical and cognitive diffusion are specified as indicators of different dynamics. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.CY (Computers and Society). However, given the emphasis on network formation and analysis, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely sub-categories.
